{% extends 'logged/_base_with_menus.tmpl' %}
{% load git_commit %}
{% block subtitle %}Homepage{% endblock %}

{% block contents %}
    <h1>Homepage</h1>
    <p>
        Here there will be the latest news, coming up deadlines, search tools. This is not done yet.
    <p>
        Meanwhile below is a changelog of what has been done recently or is to be done next.
    </p>

    <h2>Version deployed on 19/02/2020 (Staging only)</h2>
    New features, improvements:
    <ul>
        <li>Keeps and displays history for eligibility (button "Show history")</li>
        <li>Keeps history (only internally accessible) for the "Evaluation"</li>
        <li>Hides "Evaluation" for non-management users (and adds checks to avoid being miss-used)</li>
        <li>Formats budget correctly</li>
        <li>Improves presentation of the evaluation (only the basics of the proposal in a grey box)</li>
    </ul>
    We are back on the 26th February.

    <h2>Version deployed on 17/02/2020 (Staging only)</h2>
    New features:
    <ul>
        <li>Added possibility of changing the text of titles/descriptions in the proposal form depending on the Funding
            Instrument and Call. For example some funding instruments might ask "Describe your proposal" and some other
            ones
            "Describe your field trip", or "Describe your event".
        </li>
        <li>Added internal (SPI only) comments and attachments to proposals</li>
        <li>Added internal (SPI only) comments and attachments to calls</li>
        <li>Added "Project Eligibility": Yes/No and eligibility comment</li>
        <li>Reviewer mode: reviewers can only see the proposals of calls to which they have access. Creating and
            assigning
            reviewers to calls can be done only by John, Jen or Carles at the moment.
        </li>
        <li>Improved screen layout: previously there were blank spaces around some of the lists, now it uses all the
            screen (important to have space for the eligibility side column).
        </li>
        <li>Major update of the framework (Django) that the Projects application is built on (from version 2.2.6 to
            3.0.3). Minor updates of libraries that are used by the application (database, object storage, Excel writer,
            etc.)
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Version deployed on 24/01/2020</h2>
    New features:
    <ul>
        <li>Added login system for reviewers: they only have access to the list of proposals.</li>
        <li>Export list of proposals as CSV format.</li>
        <li>Added link to the proposal on the Excel evaluation spreadsheet.</li>
        <li>Renamed "Contacts" to "People". Added check/cross for the "Privacy Policy" and "Contact newsletter".</li>
        <li>Changed contact detail on the page before login since it will be used by reviewers as well.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Version deployed on 20/01/2020 and 21/01/2020</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Fixed application error when the amount column in the budget was an invalid number (e.g. text or using wrong
            thousands separator). Now it returns a form error and the applicant can fix it.
        </li>
        <li>
            Fixed: after the previous fix when the amount was empty it returned an application error.
        </li>
        <li>Fixed text in the proposal view: Agree to data policy -> privacy policy, displays the keywords in the view,
            consolidates some more text between the form and the display view.
        </li>
        <li>
            Fixed email link on the application error pages.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Version deployed on 17/01/2020</h2>
    Fixes:
    <ul>
        <li>Fixed "Date of PhD" not appearing on the proposal view</li>
        <li>Fixed problem that would have prevented an applicant creating a proposal if there were previously two
            proposals with the same applicant name with two different career stages and now this name is an
            Overarching project supervisor
        </li>
        <li>
            Fixed "Date of PhD" not being updated if the Applicant was also the Overall Project Supervisor
        </li>
    </ul>

    Improvements:
    <ul>
        <li>Date/date time picker widgets to select a date: using a Javascript widget instead of the browser's native
            widget. This works the same across all browsers (previously we had problems on Safari, Internet Explorer)
            and different operating
            systems. As well as being more intuitive now, it also gives us more control on how it looks
        </li>
        <li>Send mail notifications on Draft Saved or Draft Submitted to the applicant email address (thanks John for
            helping to create the <a href="mailto:spi-notifications@epfl.ch">spi-notifications@epfl.ch</a> email
            address)
        </li>
        <li>Added email alerts to Carles/Jen (John to be added) when certain events happen. For example if a file
            attachment
            should be available on the object storage but it's not currently accessible
        </li>
        <li>Improves "Date of PhD" month validator. "Date of PhD" is not of a date type because it doesn't include
            the day (it's saved as a string) so it needs special validation instead of the standard from the system. All
            done now.
        </li>
        <li>
            We've written <a
                href="https://c4science.ch/w/swiss_polar_institute_data_and_it_infrastructure_and_applictions/spi_projects_application/">internal
            documentation</a> on different topics about the application and <a
                href="https://c4science.ch/w/swiss_polar_institute_data_and_it_infrastructure_and_applictions/">server
            setup</a> (please follow links to see the full documentation; ask Jen or Carles if you can't access it)
        </li>
        <li>
            Added unit tests to reduce possibility of bugs and make the application easier to change
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Version deployed on 10/12/2019</h2>
    Minor changes only
    <ul>
        <li>Fixed "Overarching project" checkbox on the Call view in the management panel (was always disabled even
            though it was enabled. Cosmic change of the view only)
        </li>
        <li>Improved logo: white background and high quality logo in the management</li>
        <li>(Backend, not affecting users) Fixed unit tests after last week's changes</li>
        <li>Changed Data Collection text</li>
    </ul>

